insights: The Tata Sierra has a nod to the original Sierra with a rectangular grill and headlight design.
The car features a body color panel, 19-inch wheels, and a modern design with a lot of future elements.
The interior is all new with very few carryover parts, including a new steering wheel and gear selector knob.
The car has a 3-screen setup with a JBL speaker system and a large panoramic sunroof.
The car has ventilated seats, USB sockets, and a center console box with a 65-watt power outlet.
The car's design theme is vertical and proud, with a spoiler on top and a clean surfacing all around.
The car's infotainment system allows for individual content playback without disturbing passengers, and has a Bluetooth connection for headphones.
The car's design is a mix of old and new elements, with a nod to the original Sierra and a modern twist.
